# ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_objects (Data Source)

Lists objects in an S3 bucket using the v2 API. The response is a single page controlled by `limit`, `key_marker` and `version_id_marker`; follow `next_key_marker` (and `is_truncated`) to fetch subsequent pages.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/data-sources/ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_objects/data-source.tf"}}

## Schema

### Required

- `bucket_name` (String) Name of the bucket to list objects from
- `service_name` (String) Service name of the resource representing the id of the cloud project

### Optional

- `delimiter` (String) Character to group keys into common prefixes (directory-like listing)
- `key_marker` (String) Key to resume listing from
- `limit` (Number) Maximum number of entries to return (API hard cap: 1000)
- `prefix` (String) Return only objects whose key begins with this prefix
- `version_id_marker` (String) Version ID to resume listing from (only used when `with_versions` is true and `key_marker` is set)
- `with_versions` (Boolean) When true, list all versions (and delete markers) rather than only current objects

### Read-Only

- `is_truncated` (Boolean) Whether more objects exist beyond the current page
- `next_key_marker` (String) Key to pass as `key_marker` for the next page; empty when `is_truncated` is false
- `objects` (Attributes List) Objects, common prefixes and (when `with_versions` is set) delete markers returned for the current page

Each element of `objects` exposes the same fields as the single-object data source `ovh_cloud_storage_object_bucket_object`.
